## Public API

This feature exposes ONLY what these two files re-export:

- `frontend/src/index.ts`
- `backend/src/index.ts`

Anything not in those barrels is internal. Do not import internals from outside
the feature; if a consumer needs something, promote it through the barrel.

## Boundary rules (enforced by `yarn lint`)

- `frontend/` may import from `@internal/api-client`, `@internal/shared-types`,
  `@internal/shared-ui`, and other `packages/*` — nothing else.
  - Especially: NOT `@internal/app` / `apps/web/src/**`, NOT other `@feature/*`.
- `backend/` may import from `@internal/db`, `@internal/shared-types`, other
  `packages/*`, and other `@feature/*-backend` packages.
  - NOT `@internal/backend` / `apps/api/src/**`, NOT any `@feature/*-frontend`.

If you find yourself wanting to break a rule, lift the shared bit into
`packages/` or `@internal/shared-ui` instead.

## Where it plugs in

- Backend router mounted in `apps/api` at `/api/${{ values.name }}`.
- Frontend route declared in `apps/web/src/AppRoutes.tsx` at `/${{ values.name }}`.
- If this feature is a widget, register it in `apps/web/src/widgets/registry.tsx`.
